    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-12-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="391"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3123/7.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Swedish Chargé</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-12-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 9, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 42.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received with sincere regret your note of
                    the 8th instant anouncing the death of His Majesty King Oscar II of Sweden,
                    which took place at the royal castle at Stockholm on yesterday morning.</p>
                <p>A telegram was received at an early hour yesterday from the minister of the
                    United States at Stockholm announcing His Majesty’s death.</p>
                <p>The President at once sent a telegram to His Majesty Gustavus V, reading as
                        follows.<note n="a" xml:id="d391fna">Printed supra.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
